PrecisOrder (a) setting apart, for the use and benefit of the OCHAPOWACE INDIAN BAND, of some 246.31 hectares of land in Saskatchewan, including mines and minerals, as Ochapowace Indian Reserves Nos. 71-34, 71-35 and 71-36, and (b) consenting to the exercise by SASKATCHEWAN TELECOMMUNICATIONS of its powers to acquire an EASEMENT over some of those lands for the purposes of telephone lines, etc.
